<h1>Polyglot Privacy Policy</h1>

<h2>Introduction</h2>
<p>We at Polyglot value your privacy. This policy outlines the information we collect, how we use it, and the steps we take to protect it. By using our website, you consent to the practices outlined in this policy.</p>

<h2>Information We Collect</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Personally Identifiable Information:</strong> We may collect information you directly provide, such as your name, email address, and payment information when you create an account or make a purchase.</li>
    <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> We may collect information about how you interact with our website, including pages visited, courses taken, and time spent on the site.</li>
    <li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> We may collect information about your device and browser, such as your IP address and operating system.</li>
</ul>

<h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Providing Services:</strong> We use your information to provide and improve our language courses, process payments, and communicate with you. </li>
    <li><strong>Personalization:</strong> We may use your information to tailor your learning experience and offer recommendations.</li>
    <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> We use aggregated usage data to understand how our website is used and to make improvements.</li>
    <li><strong>Marketing:</strong> With your consent, we may send you promotional emails about Polyglot. You can opt out at any time.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Protecting Your Information</h2>
<p>We implement reasonable security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. However, no data transmission over the internet is completely secure.</p>

<h2>Third-Party Sharing</h2>
<p>We may share your information with third-party service providers who assist us in operating our website or providing our services. We do not sell your personal information to third parties.</p>

<h2>Your Rights</h2>
<p>You may have the right to access, correct, or request deletion of your personal information. Please contact us to exercise these rights.</p>

<h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
<p>Our website is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.</p>

<h2>Changes to this Policy</h2>
<p>We may update this policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page.</p>